itless white that span over 2 kilometres. Havelock Island's Radhanagar Beach has blue waves and snow-white sands. Along the shore's edge, food shops and merchants provide visitors with drinks and delicious fish to keep them refreshed. While people spend hours simply relaxing in this gorgeous wonderland, visitors can rent beach mattresses, parasols, and umbrellas. Because Radhanagar Beach Andaman is near Elephant Beach, people may see mahouts looking to take their elephants on a road trip with tourists. With lifeguards on duty and monitoring the beach, it is also safe. For visitors best time to visit:?Avoid visiting during the rainy season between September and February or between March and May. Services Both male and female changing rooms are provided. For a day may be rented locker facilities for INR 10 per locker. Travel agent There are paid showers available for INR 10 per person. Basic knowledge: According to Times magazine, this seventh-greatest beach in the world is the best in Asia. It is also referred to as Port Blair's Beach No. 7. The beach has been recognized with a Blue Flag Certificate by the United Nations Environment Programme. The Best Part Of Radhanagar Beach Sea walking Parasailing Scuba diving and Snorkelling Birdwatching Swimming Nearby Attractions 2. Cellular Jail Port Blair, the Andaman and Nicobar Islands capital, has a historic colonial jail known as The Cellular Jail, often known as "Kala Pani." Several significant freedom fighters, like Yogendra Shukla, Vinayak Damodar Savarkar, and Batukeshwar Dutt, stayed. The prison complex is currently controlled by the Indian government and is recognized as a national war memorial representing prisoner life during the British colonial era. The Cellular Jail in the Andaman Islands is a well-known tourist attraction where visitors may learn about its history and enjoy a light show created in honour of all the prisoners housed there. The Cellular Jail, an essential part of India's history, serves as a sad