 sand beaches, it is one of the most well-liked vacation destinations in the south. Water activities will help discover the abundant marine life in this area, particularly colourful coral reefs and fishes. Sitting on the sand and listening to the sound of the waves rustling is a great way to relax at Jolly Buoy Beach and on the island. Jolly Buoy Island is only possible for a day trip; the jetty that brings visitors there leaves at 9 am and returns at 2 pm because overnight stays are not permitted. Water activities on Jolly Buoy Island include scuba diving, glass-bottom boat rides, and Snorkelling. For its variety of marine life, Jolly Buoy Island is well known. In the water, there are many vibrant corals and fish communities that are visible. The significant corals spotted on Jolly buoy Island are Pacillopora, Acropora, Fungia, the Forties, Leptoseris, gorgonians, and tubipora. Because of their vivid colours and graceful movements, beautiful starfish, False Percula Clownfish, ocellaris clownfish, butterflyfishes, parrot fishes, and angel fishes are the kinds that may be easily seen. Best Time For Visit Jolly Buoy Island is only accessible to visitors for six months out of the year. Tourists can visit between November and April. Tip For Visit Plan your journey on a day other than Mondays, as there are no ferry services to Jolly Buoy Island on that day. Unless you obtain a permit from the Fisheries Department, you may bring no seashell. Jolly Buoy Island is a plastic-free zone, so make sure you don't bring any plastic items, such as carry bags. 11. Rajiv Gandhi Water Sports Complex The charming Andaman Islands provide a wide range of tourist activities to ensure visitors have a good experience. Among these locations, the Rajiv Gandhi Water Sports Complex is a must-see spot for explorers. The region offers a wide variety of thrilling water sports activities and is known as the Andaman Water Sports Complex. The Rajiv Gandhi Water Sports Complex offers a variety of spor