ll carry visitors to the shores of the stunning, lovely Parrot Island, which is just 30 minutes away so that visitors can see the return of the parrots. 14. Diglipur In the North Andaman region, there is a large island called Diglipur, a paradise for nature; the island is home to large spells of mangroves, tropical woods, and beautiful beaches with various rare marine life. The highest peak in the Andaman and Nicobar Islands, Saddle Peak, is accessible through the Saddle Peak National Park, which is located on this island. The sole river to pass through the Andamans is the Kalpon River, also located here. The 42 caves that make up the complicated labyrinth known as the Alfred Caves, located near Diglipur, can fulfil the needs of those daring enough to take on the strenuous effort of discovering and wandering through these caves. The shores of Diglipurs provide several beautiful beaches where visitors may lose themselves in the beauty of the sea all day long if they're searching for a relaxed holiday. Some Other Places To Visit Alfred Caves Mud Volcanoes or Jal Tikry Saddle Peak National Park Ram Nagar Beach Ross and Smith Island Kalipur Beach 15. Guitar Island Beach Guitar Island is one of the many unique, isolated islands that make up Andaman & Nicobar, and it's also one of the most enjoyable places to visit. This island is a beautiful day journey from the main island, with a bright blue ocean all around and leafy greens inside. These islands are famous for adventurers seeking escape from the usual tourist crowd. The group has various gem-like islands, with Guitar Island being one among them. Because of its shape, the little green patch in the azure blue of the Indian Ocean is given that name. Guitar Island looks like a guitar, with the little water sound hole in the middle, the long neck, and even the headstock seen from above. There are no stores or hotels that exist here. As a result, most visitors arrive on day trips through a 15-minute boat ride from Long Island, which is nearby. Guitar Island is serenely in the clear blue ocean, surrounded by one of the most beautiful Andaman Island scenery. How to go to the Andaman Islands By Air Andaman Veer Savarkar International Airport in Port Blair offers flights from Kolkata, Delhi, Chennai, Visakhapatnam, Hyderabad, and Bangalore. Popular airlines include Vistara, IndiGo, Air India, GoAir, SpiceJet, and others. By water If travelling by water, you can catch a ship in Chennai, Vizag, or Kolkata. The ships generally sail for three to four months for 60 to 70 hours. Next Topic>Tourist Places in Coonoor ? prev next ? For Videos Join Our Youtube Channel: Join Now Feedback Send your Feedback to [email protected] Help Others, Please Share Learn Latest Tutorials Splunk SPSS Swagger Transact-SQL Tumblr ReactJS Regex Reinforcement Learning R Programming RxJS React Native Python Design Patterns Python Pillow Python Turtle Keras Preparation Aptitude Reasoning Verbal Ability Interview Questions Company Questions Trending Technologies Artificial Intelligence AWS Selenium Cloud Computing Hadoop ReactJS Data Science Angular 7 Blockchain Git Machine Learning DevOps B.Tech / MCA DBMS Data Structures DAA Operating System Computer Network Compiler Design Computer Organization Discrete Mathematics Ethical Hacking Computer Graphics Software Engineering Web Technology Cyber Security Automata C Programming C++ Java .Net Python Programs Control System Data Mining Data Warehouse Javatpoint Services JavaTpoint offers too many high quality services. Mail us on [email protected], to get more information about given services. Website Designing Website Development Java Development PHP Development WordPress Graphic Designing Logo Digital Marketing On Page and Off Page SEO PPC Content Development Corporate Training Classroom and Online Training Data Entry Training For College Campus JavaTpoint offers college campus training on Core Java, Advance Java, .Net, Android, Hadoop, PHP, Web Technology and Python. Pleas